# Gameplay_Systems

## 1. Applies when
Always. Any game has core mechanics, state machines and numeric parameters.

## 2. This document owns
Movement; combat; stealth; damage; equipment; tools; energy; state machines; all
gameplay numbers, multipliers, cooldowns, costs, hit / damage and AI rules.

## 3. This document does NOT own
Mission structure; resource economy; character sheets; world-truth explanations.

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
0. Document role & number authority · 1. Core loop · 2. Movement · 3. Combat ·
4. Damage & survival · 5. Aiming / tools · 6. State machines · 7. TODO

## 5. Common boundaries
- Gameplay vs Character — numbers here; narrative meaning in Character.
- Gameplay vs Resource — combat energy numbers here; supply/inventory in Resource.
- Gameplay vs Mission — systems here; mission uses them, does not define them.

## 6. Common audit rules
- Single source of truth for all numbers; other docs summarise and link here.
- Character / GDD numbers must reference back to Gameplay_Systems.
